OA&oe=6A0B2825", "manifest_stream_number": 0, "is_dash_periods": true, "protocol": "https", "video_ext": "mp4", "audio_ext": "none", "abr": 0, "vbr": 780.147, "resolution": "1080x1920", "aspect_ratio": 0.56, "filesize_approx": 6172035, "http_headers": {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/143.0.0.0 Safari/537.36", "Accept": "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "format": "dash-2279765425887068v - 1080x1920 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by artificialintelligenceee", "description": "Okara AI is gaining attention for its “Think before telling AI everything” campaign, which focuses on the growing problem of shadow AI, where employees unknowingly share sensitive company data with public AI tools. \n\nAs AI becomes part of daily work, people often upload internal documents, financial records, legal files, customer information, and other confidential details without fully understanding the privacy risks involved.\n\nThe company uses this gap between user expectations and reality as its main positioning. It encourages people to pause before sharing sensitive information such as medical records, passwords, legal documents, business data, or deeply personal conversations. \n\nRather than asking users to stop using AI, Okara AI promotes using it with greater awareness and stronger privacy protection.\n\nFollow us (👉@artificialintelligenceee) for everything latest from the AI world.\n\nMedia: Okara AI", "duration": 63.291, "timestamp": 1777436369, "uploader_id": "66294766434", "uploader": "Artificial Intelligence (AI)", "channel": "artificialintelligenceee", "like_count": 17016, "comment_count": 246, "comments": [{"author": "trichm", "author_id": "1079136723", "id": "17861583783687560", "text": "Great so everyone is gonna know that I don’t know how to do math", "timestamp": 